          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and chill the pastry",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold butter into the flour and icing sugar until the mixture resembles fine breadcrumbs. Mix in the egg yolk and enough cold milk to bring it to a firm dough. Flatten into a disc, wrap, and refrigerate for 30 minutes. Roll out on a lightly floured surface to 3 mm thick and use to line a 23 cm loose-bottomed tart tin. Press into the sides, trim the overhang, and return to the refrigerator for 15 minutes. Preheat the oven to 180°C conventional.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Blind bake the case",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line the chilled pastry case with baking paper and fill with baking beans or uncooked rice. Bake for 20 minutes, then remove the paper and beans and bake for a further 8 to 10 minutes until the base is pale gold and fully dry to the touch. Reduce the oven to 150°C.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make and bake the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whisk together the eggs, egg yolks, and sugar until combined. Add the cream, lemon juice, and zest and whisk until smooth. Place the tart tin on a baking tray and pour the filling directly into the hot case, this minimises the time the filling is in an unbaked case. Bake at 150°C for 25 to 30 minutes until set at the edges with a gentle wobble at the centre. Leave to cool to room temperature in the tin before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
